<subSubSection id="C374652CFFE0FF88D4CCF8E00816FB56" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFE0FF88D4CCF8E009B5FD5E" blockId="29.[151,1437,1867,2038]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,151,1258]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFE0FF8BD4CCF8E00C01F8F6" bold="true" box="[199,345,1867,1893]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFE0FF8BD569F8E70CC4F8F5" box="[354,412,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Male</emphasis>
(IAvH-I-2974). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE0FF8BD6EFF8E70E29F8F4" box="[740,881,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1846,1870]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,274,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-67@27.[151,1436,273,1823]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-2974): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (IAvH-I-2975): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520776/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace brown-reddish with dark brown margins. Chelicerae brown with dark paturon base, fangs brown-reddish. Endites light brown, white on anterior region. Labium and sternum light brown. Legs: coxae I–IV light yellow. Femora-tarsi light brown. Abdomen: dorsally dark gray with nine white guanine spots organized as follows: four spots are dispositioned on anterior side: two rounded, central and are fused on medial region, and two lateral and wide, extending to ventral region; two central and rounded spots larger than previous ones, anteriorly projected, on sub-medial positioned; two very long and transversal bands, extending to ventral region, medially positioned; a large transversal spot, posteriorly positioned. Laterally dark gray spots as above. Ventrally pale beige. Spinnerets light brown. Measurements: total length 3.26, carapace length 1.67, width 1.10, height 0.56. Clypeus height 0.32. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.07, ALE 0.08, PME 0.09, PLE 0.09; AME–AME 0.14, AME–ALE 0.17, AME–PME 0.21, PME–PME 0.17, PME–PLE 0.25, ALE–PLE 0.20. Chelicerae 0.55 length. Sternum length 0.68, width 0.66. Legs: I—femur 1.08/ patella 0.36/ tibia 0.91/ metatarsus 0.84/ tarsus 0.47/ total 3.66; II—0.94/ 0.40/ 0.70/ 0.62/ 0.41/ 3.07; III—0.85/ 0.35/ 0.63/ 0.76/ 0.39/ 2.98; IV—1.16/ 0.37/ 0.95/ 1.30/ 0.69/ 4.47. Abdomen length 1.38. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): III—tibia v1r-0-2, metatarsus v1r-0-1r; IV—tibia v1r-1r-2. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (RPC) wide, external edge rounded; tegulum (T) rounded, almost as wide as long; subtegulum (St) longer than wide, external edge rounded, small ventral projection; conductor (C) developed, long, thin sclerotized region at distal side; appendix (ApC) long, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, wide at base, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (EB) approximately as long as four times basal tegular membrane; basal tegular membrane (BTM) very short, apically rounded; spermatic ducts (SD) S-shaped, anterior fold closed, very wide, posterior fold open, thin; ventral tibial apophysis (VTA) short, apically straight; median apophysis (MA) laminar, long, apically folded; retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) conical almost as long as palpal tibia, apically sharp (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE3FF88D7F9FD1809D8FD5E" box="[1010,1152,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[349,1239,189,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@28.[349,1239,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-2974): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-2975): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520780/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 16A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE3FF88D087FD1809B9FD5E" box="[1164,1249,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1689,1713]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,186,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-19@29.[151,1436,181,1666]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 17. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-2974): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-2975): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; S, spermathecae; St, subtegulum; SR, seminal receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520782" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520782/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">17A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFE3FF88D4CCFD7C0DA1FB32" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1258]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFE3FF88D4CCFD7C0C43FD62" box="[199,283,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Female</emphasis>
(IAvH-I-2975). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE3FF88D668FD7C0FA8FD62" box="[611,752,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1846,1870]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,274,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-67@27.[151,1436,273,1823]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-2974): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (IAvH-I-2975): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520776/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 15C–D</figureCitation>
): Coloration and abdominal spots pattern as male, carapace dark brown with Y-shaped paler spot anterior to fovea. Abdomen with separated central spots. Measurements: total length 4.20, carapace length 2.02, width 1.27, height 0.91. Clypeus height 0.41. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.08, ALE 0.09, PME 0.09, PLE 0.11; AME–AME 0.14, AME–ALE 0.17, AME–PME 0.22, PME–PME 0.20, PME–PLE 0.36, ALE–PLE 0.21. Chelicerae 0.58 length. Sternum length 0.79, width 0.78. Legs: I—femur 1.15/ patella 0.46/ tibia 1.05/ metatarsus 0.85/ tarsus 0.62/ total 4.13; II—0.96/ 0.36/ 0.73/ 0.77/ 0.59/ 3.41; III—0.95/ 0.41/ 0.60/ 0.80/ 0.52/ 3.28; IV—1.31/ 0.46/ 0.99/ 1.37/ 0.74/ 4.87. Abdomen length 2.16. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—tibia v1r-0-0, metatarsus v2-0-2; II—metatarsus v1r-0-2; III—tibia v2-1p-2. Epigyne: lateral borders (LB) short, posteriorly positioned, delimiting rounded atrium (A); median field plate (MFP) wider than long, basal edge rounded; copulatory ducts (CD) very short, wide, almost undistinguished from spermathecae; seminal receptacles (SR) long, thin, curved towards median septum; spermathecae (S) large, rounded, posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts (FD) approximately as long as spermathecae length (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE3FF88D119FBC808C0FBEE" box="[1298,1432,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[349,1239,189,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@28.[349,1239,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 16. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-2974): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-2975): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520780/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 16E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFE3FF88D49CFB2C0DB5FB32" box="[151,237,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1689,1713]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,186,1651]" captionTargetId="figure-19@29.[151,1436,181,1666]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 17. Tenedos ayo sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-2974): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-2975): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; S, spermathecae; St, subtegulum; SR, seminal receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520782" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520782/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">17C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFE3FF88D4CCFB010816FB56" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,1258]" box="[199,1358,1194,1221]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
